article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. -- — Anthony Pritchard scored 18 points as Central Michigan beat Miami (Ohio) 71-55 on Tuesday night. Pritchard had seven rebounds and eight assists for the Chippewas (10-9, 5-2 Mid-American Conference). Brian Taylor scored 14 points, going 5 of 9 and 4 of 4 from the free throw line. Markus Harding had 11 points and went 5 of 8 from the field. Darweshi Hunter led the way for the RedHawks (9-10, 3-4) with 16 points. Anderson Mirambeaux added 13 points for Miami (OH). Mekhi Cooper also had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
